3. cs.SL (Speech and Language Processing): The paper deals with improving speech recognition, which is a subfield of speech and language processing. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves designing linear-phase filters to adapt simulated impulse responses, which is a machine learning technique. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not deal with computer vision, it is possible that the techniques used in the paper could be applied to computer vision problems as well.
